post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_20161535_20163170_0": {"length": 12, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 110}}, "n3337": {"so_20161535_20163170_0": {"length": 12, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 105}}, "n4659": {"so_20161535_20163170_0": {"length": 12, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 114}}}, "20161535": {"ViewCount": "1277", "Body": "<p>I want to create a class with a template constructor:</p>\n<pre><code>class foo\n{\n    template &lt;class T&gt; foo(T var) {}\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>This compiles in VS2008, but I have no idea if it is a non-standard extension, or if the C++ standard allows it.</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "20163170", "Title": "Does the C++ standard allow a template constructor for a non-template class?", "CreationDate": "2013-11-23T11:05:50.730", "Id": "20161535", "CommentCount": "7", "FavoriteCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2013-11-23T13:55:50.587", "Score": "6", "OwnerUserId": "492336", "Tags": "<c++><templates><constructor>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "20163170": {"Id": "20163170", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>In [temp.mem]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_20161535_20163170_0\">A template can be declared within a class or class template; such a\n  template is called a member template.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Constructors are members and it isn't explicitly disallowed to make them templates.</p>\n<p>For example, <code>std::shared_ptr</code> has many <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/memory/shared_ptr/shared_ptr\">template constructors</a>.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-11-23T13:55:50.587", "Score": "6", "CreationDate": "2013-11-23T13:55:50.587", "ParentId": "20161535", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "634175"}});